    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/08-agents-harness/07-multi-agent-systems.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Multiple agents buy you three things a single call cannot: escape from one context window, error isolation with checkpoint/retry, and parallelism across independent sub-tasks; ensembling gain 1-(1-p)^N is largest at moderate per-agent success p.; The five canonical topologies (orchestrator-worker star, pipeline chain, debate peer-to-peer, blackboard shared-state, hierarchical tree) each have a signature failure mode; real systems compose them.; The workflow-vs-agent distinction is about WHO owns control flow: in a workflow the next step is decided by developer code (deterministic branches), in an agent the next step is decided by the model's own output; frameworks sit at different points on this axis.; Orchestrator-worker mechanics: decompose into a structured JSON plan, fan out workers in parallel with isolated error handling, then synthesize \u2014 the orchestrator's context is the bottleneck, which the blackboard externalizes.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  workflow-vs-agent-control-flow-spectrum, multi-agent-tax-compounding, ensembling-gain-vs-p\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
